81
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:55,680
With app store optimization, there are three basic steps.

82
00:04:55,680 --> 00:05:01,680
Step one, you want to find, in this [music] case, location specific keywords, things like New York subway,

83
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:02,800
Chicago train.

84
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:06,080
Add those to the title and metadata of the app.

85
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:11,759
That will start process of the appearing in searches for those specific keywords.

86
00:05:11,759 --> 00:05:15,680
But it wasn't until I did some research that growth really happened.

87
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:20,240
First of all, I can see that different cities use different terminology.

88
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:23,680
So, for example, in New York, you've got the MTA subway.

89
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:26,880
In Chicago, you have the CTA L train.

90
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:31,520
Once I started adding these kind of keywords, [music] I found that downloads increased substantially.

91
00:05:31,520 --> 00:05:36,000
At the same time, also updated screenshots, so they're much more locationsp specific.

92
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:44,000
So each localization would have its own set of screenshots to hone in on the fact that this app works for where you are right now.

93
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:47,039
The next step was to use other localizations.

94
00:05:47,039 --> 00:05:58,080
So, for example, if you were to add keywords to Mexican Spanish, those same keywords would be indexed for the US app store and have the same weight as [music] the native US English localization.

95
00:05:58,080 --> 00:06:02,000
Step two was to find more keywords that worked.

96
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,199
You have two choices.

97
00:06:03,199 --> 00:06:08,960
You can use Apple Search Ads, start testing a few keywords at a time to see which ones convert,

98
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:10,880
or using the app store itself.

99
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:18,560
Search for terms, keywords, and phrases around what your app does by typing in the first few characters into search.

100
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:25,120
You'll see a list come up, and most people when you start typing, we'll see the list appear and tap on the first or second entry.

101
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:32,000
So, by looking at those lists, I was able to determine what are the most high impact keywords people are searching for.

102
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:38,000
And the best thing about this is is because they are very specific, they don't have a huge popularity.

103
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:46,240
So by targeting those keywords specifically in the right place at the right time, you can quite easily get into [music] the top five for a keyword.

104
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:49,360
And step three, asking for ratings within the [music] app.

105
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:53,520
At this point, you should be at the top 10 for the keywords you're looking to target.

106
00:06:53,520 --> 00:06:57,600
If an app wants to get to number one, it needs ratings [music] coming in all the time.

107
00:06:57,600 --> 00:07:01,199
